--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 512a72de08c75cf4e8a8424f7b75a271, type: 3}
  m_Name: D2T10_IndianTheftInvestigation
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  npc: 1
  sequence:
  - dialogueText: Crates? I know nothing of any crates. I have been sitting here,
      enjoying the atmosphere
    buttonText: Boss is fuming
  - dialogueText: A shame. But why involve me? I am just a traveler with a taste
      for fine service.
    buttonText: You lied
  - dialogueText: I offered a job. You accepted. We both profited. That is how the
      world turns.
    buttonText: He'll find out
  - dialogueText: If he does, he finds a thief and a buyer. We are on the same side
      of the coin now.
    buttonText: I'm dead
  - dialogueText: Only if you speak. If I fall, I take the man who did the heavy
      lifting with me.
    buttonText: You'd tell?
  - dialogueText: I prefer silence. It's cheaper. Go back, tell him you found nothing.
      For both our sakes.
    buttonText: I'll do that
